.TH WIRGLOO 1 "2026-05-22" "wirgloo" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wirgloo \- self-hosted web IRC client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wirgloo
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wirgloo
is a single-binary web IRC client. It serves a browser-based IRC interface
and proxies IRC connections over WebSocket, so users can connect to any IRC
network from a plain browser without installing anything.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS HTTP server
.TP
.BI \-addr " address"
TCP address to listen on.
Default: \fB0.0.0.0:6677\fR.
.TP
.BI \-base " path"
Base path prefix for all routes when running behind a reverse proxy,
e.g. \fB/wirgloo\fR. Leading slash and trailing slash are normalised
automatically. Default: empty (serve from \fB/\fR).
.TP
.B \-dev
Serve static files from disk instead of the embedded copy. Useful during
development: HTML, CSS and JS changes are visible without rebuilding the
binary.
.SS Session
.TP
.BI \-session-timeout " duration"
How long an IRC session survives a browser disconnect before the underlying
IRC connection is torn down. Accepts Go duration syntax, e.g. \fB30m\fR,
\fB2h\fR.
Default: \fB60m\fR.
.TP
.BI \-buffer-max " n"
Maximum number of IRC messages buffered per session while the browser is
disconnected. Buffered messages are flushed to the browser on reconnect.
Default: \fB500\fR.
.TP
.BI \-list-preview " n"
Maximum number of channels returned by \fB/list\fR before a filter is
applied, sorted by user count.
Default: \fB50\fR.
.SS Logging
.TP
.BI \-log-level " level"
Minimum log level. One of \fBdebug\fR, \fBinfo\fR, \fBwarn\fR, \fBerror\fR.
Default: \fBinfo\fR.
.TP
.B \-log-json
Emit logs as JSON instead of human-readable text. Useful for log aggregation
pipelines.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start with default settings:
.RS
.EX
wirgloo
.EE
.RE
Listen on a specific address, behind a reverse proxy at \fB/chat\fR:
.RS
.EX
wirgloo \-addr 127.0.0.1:6677 \-base /chat
.EE
.RE
Development mode with debug logging:
.RS
.EX
wirgloo \-dev \-log-level debug
.EE
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/wirgloo.service
Example systemd unit file, installed by \fBmake install-service\fR.
